comment_data.body:
Looks like the same issue as reported in https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/issues/4620.

/fyi @devoncarew
The interesting bit here is that it is specific to iOS. That wasn't mentioned in #4620.
I can't reproduce this using the iOS simulator. I'm using version 48 of the Flutter plugin but I have not installed the latest stable Flutter SDK yet. @pq can you repro this with SDK 1.20?

I tried it on a couple of iPhone devices. Another weird thing - 
- It *is happening* on iPhone 6s with iOS 13.5.1
- It is *not happening* on iPhone 5s with iOS 12.4.8.

Also see this comment - https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/63082#issuecomment-669958023. It seems @TahaTesser was able to repro this as well (perhaps on iPhone 11 simulator with iOS 13.6, as per their flutter doctor)

@animeshjain 
I've reproduced it on physical device 
From my logs
```
Launching lib/main.dart on Taha’s iPhone in debug mode...
Automatically signing iOS for device deployment using specified development team in Xcode project: X8NNQ9CYL2
Running pod install...
Running Xcode build...
Xcode build done.                                           16.5s
Installing and launching...
Waiting for Taha’s iPhone to report its views...
Debug service listening on ws://localhost:51475/ws
Syncing files to device Taha’s iPhone...
flutter: counter = 0


flutter: counter = 1


flutter: counter = 2


flutter: counter = 3


flutter: counter = 4


flutter: counter = 5


flutter: counter = 6


flutter: counter = 7


flutter: counter = 8


flutter: counter = 9



```

Interesting - I see that https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/63082 was closed referencing this issue.

From my understanding of the above:
- it repros with some iOS versions and not others
- it repros with Android Studio but not VS Code

The first item would led me to think that this is an issue w/ the flutter runtime, or, the flutter tools mechanism for getting stdout from the running app.

The 2nd item would lead me to think that this is an Android Studio specific issue. 

We'll likely need a bit more info about places where it definitely does and doesn't repro. cc @zanderso to see if he's seem similar reports for extra newlines in output from apps running on iOS.
Definitely happening on an iPhone XS Max using update from 07 Aug 2020.

I have same issue after I updated Flutter 1.17.x to 1.20.x
iPhone 11. iOS 13.5.1 (real device)
iOS version is same with @animeshjain

This started with/around 1.18.0, was not happening in 1.17.0
Not sure if this is related to the IntelliJ plugin or Flutter itself, might be a mix of both.
Note - this might be the same issue as https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/59820.

title: print command is adding extra new lines to every output in the console for iOS
